        {
            "id": "te_news:446887:0",
            "title": "Sweden Inflation Rate Rises to 1% in January",
            "description": "<div class=\"body-KX2tCBZq body-pIO_GYwT content-pIO_GYwT\"><span><p class=\"\">The annual inflation rate in Sweden rose to 1% in January 2025, up from 0.8% in December and missed market expectations of a slowdown to 0.5%, according to preliminary estimates.</p><p class=\"\">Despite the increase, this marked the sixth consecutive period with inflation below the Riksbank’s 2% target.</p><p class=\"\">On a monthly basis, consumer prices were unchanged, as in the previous month, defying forecasts of a 0.6% decline.</p><p class=\"\">Meanwhile, the annual CPI with a fixed interest rate (the central bank’s target measure) rose by 2.2%, the highest since May last year, well above the expected 1.6% increase and accelerating from 1.5% in December.</p><p class=\"\">On a monthly basis, it rose by 0.4%, compared to forecasts of a 0.2% decline and a 0.3% rise in the previous period.</p></span></div>",
            "link": "https://www.tradingview.com/news/te_news:446887:0-sweden-inflation-rate-rises-to-1-in-january/",
            "pub_date": "2025-02-06 15:09:19",
            "source": "Trading Economics",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
        {
