        {
            "id": "urn:newsml:mtnewswires.com:20250206:G2464359:0",
            "title": "Market Chatter: JD.com Renews Interest in Germany-Based Electronics Retailer Ceconomy",
            "description": "<div class=\"body-KX2tCBZq body-pIO_GYwT content-pIO_GYwT\"><span><p class=\"\">JD.com  revived its interest in purchasing Germany-based electronics retail company Ceconomy, Bloomberg News reported Wednesday, citing people familiar with the matter. </p><p class=\"\">The Chinese e-commerce giant has already approached Ceconomy itself and its shareholders, the report said, citing the sources. </p><p class=\"\">JD.com has been on the lookout for potential acquisitions to expand itself as it faces a weak Chinese economy. Among the deals it studied was with UK-based electronics retailer Currys, but the deal fell off, the report said. </p><p class=\"\">A Ceconomy spokesperson declined to comment, the news agency said, while a JD.com representative did not respond immediately to queries. </p><p class=\"\">(Market Chatter news is derived from conversations with market professionals globally. This information is believed to be from reliable sources but may include rumor and speculation. Accuracy is not guaranteed.)</p></span></div>",
            "link": "https://www.tradingview.com/news/mtnewswires.com:20250206:G2464359:0/",
            "pub_date": "2025-02-06 15:05:10",
            "source": "MT Newswires",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
        {
            "id": "urn:newsml:mtnewswires.com:20250206:G2464345:0",
            "title": "CMS Info Systems' Consolidated Profit Climbs in Fiscal Q3",
            "description": "<div class=\"body-KX2tCBZq body-pIO_GYwT content-pIO_GYwT\"><span><p class=\"\">CMS Info Systems  said its consolidated profit attributable to owners rose to 931.9 million Indian rupees in the fiscal third quarter from 870.8 million rupees a year ago, according to an Indian bourse filing on Wednesday by the IT company. </p><p class=\"\">Earnings per share during the quarter ended Dec. 31, 2024, climbed to 5.56 rupees from 5.37 rupees a year earlier. </p><p class=\"\">Revenue from operations in fiscal Q3 slipped year on year to 5.81 billion rupees from 5.82 billion rupees.</p></span></div>",
            "link": "https://www.tradingview.com/news/mtnewswires.com:20250206:G2464345:0/",
            "pub_date": "2025-02-06 15:05:18",
            "source": "MT Newswires",
